## OBS & Streaming — Known Issues & Fixes

> Learned March 2026. Root cause of all issues: AERO X16 display is 2560×1600 (16:10), OBS canvas is 1920×1080 (16:9). Aspect ratio mismatch causes black bars on all display captures. Every fix below traces back to this.

### The Core Problem
- **AERO X16 native display:** 2560×1600 — 16:10 aspect ratio
- **OBS canvas:** 1920×1080 — 16:9 aspect ratio
- Any capture of the full display will letterbox or pillarbox into the canvas
- Fix differs by scene type — see below

---

### WoW Broadcast Scene

**Problem:** WoW runs at 2560×1600 in Fullscreen (Windowed) mode, producing black bars on the left and right sides of the OBS canvas.

**What doesn't work:**
- Changing WoW resolution to 1920×1080 is blocked in Fullscreen (Windowed) — it matches desktop resolution only
- Switching to true Fullscreen (which unlocks resolution options) breaks UI addon layouts

**Fix in place:** Right-click WoW source in OBS → Transform → **Stretch to Screen**. Slight geometric distortion (16:10 → 16:9) but imperceptible in gameplay. Zero bars.

**Better long-term fix:** Crop/Pad filter — 80px left, 80px right — crops to 16:9 without distortion. Needs testing to dial in exact values.

**Camera:** Currently bottom-left. Bottom-right is cleaner — less overlap with WoW UI elements which cluster on the left.

---

### Notion Writing Scene

**Problem:** Display Capture at 2560×1600 produces black bars top and bottom in the 1920×1080 canvas.

**Fix in place (current):** Before streaming, drop Windows display resolution to 1920×1080 (right-click desktop → Display settings → Resolution). Use Display Capture. Change back to 2560×1600 after stream. Takes ~10 seconds each way.

**Long-term fix:** Use ASUS ZenScreen (1920×1080, already in kit) as dedicated broadcast display. Notion lives on ZenScreen. OBS Display Captures ZenScreen. AERO display handles OBS, chat, controls. No resolution toggling ever. Blocked currently by USB-C port conflict with hub — resolve port situation first.

**What was ruled out:**
- FancyZones (PowerToys) — more overhead for same result as resolution toggle
- Window Capture sized to 1920×1080 — requires FancyZones to constrain window, adds complexity

---

### Camera / USB

- **Facecam MK.2** connects via USB-C on the camera end but ships with a USB-C to USB-A cable — plugs into any USB-A port. Does not require USB-C on the host side.
- Port crunch on the AERO is a known issue. Anker 7-in-1 hub is the fix — confirm it's in the chain before every stream.

---

### ZenScreen Upgrade Path (When Port Situation Is Resolved)

Once the USB-C port conflict is sorted, the ZenScreen becomes the broadcast display permanently:
- Notion (and any other writing/reading content) lives on ZenScreen during writing segments
- OBS Display Captures ZenScreen — always 1920×1080, always clean
- AERO display handles everything else: OBS controls, chat, gaming
- Game scenes use Game Capture (not display capture) — unaffected by display resolution entirely
- No resolution toggling, no Stretch to Screen, no crop math — ever again

